{{use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = ALB | NOCname = [[National Olympic Committee of Albania]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1972 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = &nbsp;{{sq icon}} | location = [[Munich]] | competitors = 5 (4 men and 1 woman) | sports = 2 | flagbearer = [[Afërdita Tusha]] (Shooting) | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1972 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[People's Socialist Republic of Albania|Albania]]''' competed at the [[Summer Olympic Games]] for the first time at the '''[[1972 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Munich]], [[West Germany]]. Five competitors, four men and one woman, took part in three events in two sports.<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ALB/summer/1972/ |title=Albania at the 1972 Munich Summer Games |accessdate=7 February 2016 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>
==Shooting== {{main|Shooting at the 1972 Summer Olympics}} Four shooters, three men and one woman, represented Albania in 1972.
