{{Distinguish|Planet Ice Arena Milton Keynes}} The '''Arena MK''' is a multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[Milton Keynes]], [[Buckinghamshire]], [[England]] and is located beside [[Stadium MK]]. The {{convert|3420|sqm|sqft}} multi-use event space is positioned over three floors and anticipates music and sporting events, conferences and exhibitions and parties.<ref name="fionao'hara">{{cite web|url=http://www.mkdons.com/news/article/arena-stadiummk-opens-its-doors-1362921.aspx|title=arena: stadiummk opens its doors|author=Fiona O'Hara|work=Milton Keynes Dons Football Club}}</ref>
Arena MK was to be the home of the [[Milton Keynes Lions]] professional [[basketball]] team. However, the retail developments that would have provided enabling funding were deferred due to lack of financing, leaving the Lions without a home.<ref>[http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/sport/Winkelman-can39t-guarantee-arena.4735321.jp Winkelman can't guarantee arena!] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090108054055/http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/sport/Winkelman-can39t-guarantee-arena.4735321.jp |date=8 January 2009 }} – MK Citizen 26 November 2008</ref> Following the conclusion of the 2011–12 season, the Lions could not secure a venue within Milton Keynes, resulting in a move south to the [[Copper Box]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/sport/other-sport/revealed-lions-to-leave-milton-keynes-for-olympic-park-in-london-1-4140859 | title=Lions to leave Milton Keynes | publisher=MK Citizen | date=9 August 2012}}</ref>
It officially opened on 8 February 2014 when it hosted the [[2014 English National Badminton Championships]].<ref name="fionao'hara"/> The Arena has hosted the [[Professional Darts Corporation]]'s [[Masters (darts)|Masters]] tournament since 2015.
In September 2018, [[Marshall Amplification]] announced agreement with Arena MK to use the space for music events, rebranding it the '''Marshall Arena'''.<ref name=Marshall>[https://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/news/welcome-to-the-marshall-arena-in-milton-keynes-1-8651333 Welcome to the Marshall Arena in Milton Keynes], [[Milton Keynes Citizen]], 29 September 2018</ref> The opening act is to be [[Black Eyed Peas]].<ref name=Marshall />
