{{Infobox football biography |name = Bajram Jashanica |image = Loko skndrb 20.jpg |image_size = 250 |caption = Jashanica with [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] in October 2015 |fullname = Bajram Jashanica |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|9|25|df=yes}} |birth_place = [[Vranidoll]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]] |height = {{convert|1.90|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Defender (association football)|Centre back]] |currentclub = [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] |clubnumber = 5 |youthyears1 = 2005–2009 |youthclubs1 = [[KF Hysi|Hysi]] |years1 = 2009–2013 |clubs1 = [[KF Hysi|Hysi]] |caps1 = 80 |goals1 = 5 |years2 = 2013–2018 |clubs2 = [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] |caps2 = 89 |goals2 = 4 |years3 = 2013–2014 |clubs3 = → [[Besa Kavajë]] (loan) |caps3 = 23 |goals3 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2014–2017 |nationalteam1 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps1 = 7 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |club-update = 9 February 2018 |nationalteam-update = 9 October 2017 }} '''Bajram Jashanica''' (born 25 September 1990) is an [[Kosovo Albanian]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who is contracted to [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] in the [[Albanian Superliga]], but is banned from football until February 2020 after he tested positive in anti-doping testing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/tjeter-goditje-e-rende-per-skenderbeun-jashanica-denohet-2-vite/|title=Tjetër goditje e rëndë për Skënderbeun, Jashanica dënohet 2 vite|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Panorama Sport]]|date=5 April 2018}}</ref> Prior to his ban, he also played for the [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo national team]] and made his international debut for Kosovo in May 2014, at the age of 23.
==Early life== Jashanica was born in Vranidoll, SFR Yugoslavia from [[Kosovo Albanian]] parents. His family with originally from [[Jasenica (Žitorađa)|Jasenica]], [[Serbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bujanoci.net/shperngulja-e-shqiptareve-prej-sanxhakut-me-1878-1912-qazim-meta/|title=Shpërngulja e shqiptarëve prej Sanxhakut më 1878-1912|quote=Albanian villages in Serbia, in which is also Jashanica family origin, which you can see in his surname Jashanica and his village Jasenica|language=Albanian|website=Bujanoci|date=18 April 2015}}</ref>
==Club career== ===Skënderbeu Korçë=== At the end of the 2014–15 he renewed his contract with Skënderbeu Korçë for another two years alongside fellow Kosovar Albanian player [[Leonit Abazi]]. The contract was signed on 5 June 2015, and it the two–year contract would keep Jashanica at the club until at least 2017, but with the option of another year as well.<ref>[http://sportekspres.com/leviz-skenderbeu-firmosin-abazi-dhe-jashanica/ Lëviz Skënderbeu, firmosin Abazi dhe Jashanica]</ref>
On 22 October 2015. Jashanica netted in a header from a corner assisted by teammate [[Bernard Berisha]] in a 5–1 away defeat against Sporting Lisbon in the [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League]] group stage. That was the first ever goal that [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] have scored in a major tournament.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://borozani.com/artikulli/jashanica-shenon-skenderbeu-mposhtet|title=Jashanica shënon, Skënderbeu mposhtet|publisher=Borozani.com|language=Albanian|date=22 October 2015|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref>
==International career== On 19 May 2014, Jashanica received a call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] for the [[Exhibition game|friendly matches]] against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] and [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/dy-miqesoret-bunjaku-shpall-listen-e-kosoves/|title=Dy miqësoret, Bunjaku shpall listën e Kosovës|language=Albanian|publisher= [[Panorama Sport]]|date= 19 May 2014}}</ref> On 21 May 2014, he made his debut with Kosovo in friendly match against Turkey after coming on as a substitute at 80th minute in place of [[Mehmet Hetemaj]].
