{{use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = CMR | NOCname = [[Cameroon Olympic and Sports Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1976 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.cnosc.org }}&nbsp;{{fr icon}} | location = [[Montreal]] | competitors = 4 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1964 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
During the '''[[1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]], Canada, '''[[Cameroon]]''', along with many other African countries, boycotted due to the participation of [[New Zealand at the 1976 Summer Olympics|New Zealand]], who still had sporting links with [[South Africa]].
Athletes from Cameroon, [[Egypt at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Egypt]], [[Morocco at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Morocco]] and [[Tunisia at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Tunisia]] competed on 18–20 July before these nations withdrew from the Games.
